content.description: Start just left of "Ring of Fire".  Climb low angle wide, awkward crack up to ledge.  Then stay to the right and ascend the wide bombay chimney to OW crack to top, continue to anchor on "Man in Black".  Kinda burly.  Can escape the last wide bit by stepping to the left and finishing on "Man in Black".
content.protection: Standard Rack up to #4 Camalot or similar.
content.location: Wide left slanting crack to the left of "Ring of Fire".  Rappel from anchor on "Man in Black".

content.description: Steep techy moves lead to some long reaches and clips. Steep moves give way to thin face crimps. The third bolt seemed like a stretch. Getting onto the face is tricky.
content.location: On the west facing side of Jonny Cash. Lots of shade  , privacy and cow pies.

content.description: A nice easy way to get to the top of Johnny Cash.  Start at the same place as "Cash Crack", then go up and right following the smaller crack system diagonalling up to the arete.  Sling the horn, then join the lower angle face/crack of "Country Trash" and head for the anchor on "Ring of Fire".
content.protection: Gear should include small cams and a 2 or 3 camalot (or similar) for the wider crack after joining "Country Trash".  A sling for the horn on the arete.
content.location: Located to the right of "Cash Crack" and around the arete to the left of "Country Trash".  Rappel from anchor on "Ring of Fire".

content.description:
Kinda gritty down low.  Pass a couple of bolts protecting some semi insecure face moves.

Finger size-ish cracks and face climbing lead to the summit.

(Mike is the man in black...ha ha).
content.protection: Initial moves protected by two bolts on the face.  Then a smallish selection of cams protect the rest of the route.
content.location:
On the northern side of the east face.

Climbs the first probable (ie, not severely overhanging) terrain to the right of Five Feet High and Rising.

Use Ring of Fire or another top anchor to get down.

content.description: Trickier than it looks. Thin moves followed by jugs. Climb past chains if TR'ing Ring Of Fire is desired.
content.location: On the east facing side of Jonny Cash facing Beef Butte.

content.description:
Fun, short route with a sunny aspect.

Start with a steep pull of the deck with smooth feet.  Crimp the crispy patina edges then relax as your feet catch up.

Couple body length to the first bolt.  Take care.

Clip the first bolt, up on nice face moves, clip second bolt then head up for a run to the juggies.
content.protection:
Two lead bolts down low.

I believe there's now a two bolt anchor on the route.  Originally, pro could be had whilst heading to the summit of the formation (1-3 Camalot or equivalent).
content.location:
Located on the narrow, due south face of the formation.  Nice flat staging area.

Rappel route (or, one of the other routes).

content.description: Just to the right of Ring of Fire. Plug a few small pieces up the crack and step left into the runnel passing two bolts to the top.
